social_posts.post_text: Love this placement, thanks for your trust Kayli!

Had the honor of tattooing another one of my talented friend @permabunny.ink’s illustrations. I couldn’t be happier with how this turned out! Swipe for close ups and to see Heidi’s original artwork.

Thank you Christina for sitting through so many dots! 

(A note on this collab - I don’t typically tattoo work that I haven’t designed myself (with the occasional exception of old engravings/vintage illustrations) but Heidi and I feel that our work meshes really well together ~ If you’re interested in getting one of their designs tattooed, they have tattoo tickets available to purchase on their website! Please note that that doesn’t guarantee your ability to book with me, but I’m always down to discuss doing more of her work whenever I have an open booking period).
Matching apples from my flash for Lesley and Momo ~ Thanks so much for coming in, you two! 🍎 🍎
More rocks, what else is new! Love filling gaps like this. Thank you Meredith!

“Celestial Arch” from my flash on two lovely clients. I ended up making this piece repeatable after it got a lot of attention during my booking period. Originally booked it three times but the last person cancelled, so it’s just these two! I might do it one final time in the future, but for now I’m loving how these both turned out. Thank you Madisyn and Kayla !
Imagined Thistle from my flash for Mar! Swipe to see different angles and a healed pic of a small piece we did about a year ago (didn’t mean to add the healed one twice but oh well).
Merry Christmas, here’s a flash preview! These new flash pieces + a few more will be available to book on Dec 27th @ 10am PST for Jan 2023. ✨ Happy holigays to you and yours ✨

My books are opening tomorrow (12/27) at 10am PST! Here are the final two flash pages that I will have available. Booking info is in my highlights but please don’t submit a form before 10am tomorrow. Can’t wait to tat you in the new yearrrrrr!!!

That’s a wrap, folks! I did over 200 tattoos this year and I’ve never been more proud of the work I’ve been doing. A billion thank you’s to all who got tattooed in 2022, this work continues to bring so much joy and meaning to my life and I can’t wait to enter my 5th (!!!) year of tattooing. 

Outside of work, this year was filled with a lot of love and a lot of loss as well. As my 20s come to an end, I’m holding so much gratitude for who I am, for the directions I continue to grow and the ways I continue to love. Im so grateful for the people in my life and I’m looking forward to a new year of continued growth and the ongoing deepening of my relationship with myself through all of the grief and love and joy that is to come. 

Love you all, thanks for tuning in. 🖤

A couple tats from the last stretch of 2022. Grass flash on two clients, the first one was adjusted slightly to flow in a specific direction. The second photo is the original piece 3 weeks into healing on another client! My fav thing about both of these is that they each perfectly frame a freckle.
Custom pomegranate for Victoria, thanks so much! Above a cute little bat by @flyingfishtattoo .
Super into this one, thank you Sarah! Swipe for a wrappy video.

Sardines! Thank you Leah, love how it turned out. I’m doing this design a few more times, can’t wait to see where y’all put these cute little fishies.
My shopmate let me put a dagger on their face!! 😱 What an honor, thank you! 🗡
Little pattern from my flash for a sweet return client (other work on this leg not by me)
It’s been so fun letting people choose which rocks to pair together from my flash book! Thanks for coming back in, Emma 🪨

Flash has been dropped and books have been opened! Booking link is in my bio, make sure you are using my general booking form and not trying to book a secret flash appointment ~ I will be booking for APRIL this round. Thank you!

After over a year long gap, I am finally restarting Queer Figure Drawing! I loved our first session back in 2021 but Covid/life got in the way and this project got pushed to the side. I’m so excited to offer this again, now with the help of my friend Danni at @daffodillstudios who is graciously offering their space to host this event (Daffodill is an independent ceramic studio that offers a whole bunch of creative classes and workshops, make sure to check them out!) 

Figure drawing is an excellent way to practice observational drawing. Sessions include a variety of quick gestures, short poses, and a few medium/longer poses. Bring a sketchbook or paper on a drawing board and your medium of choice (charcoal, pencils, or markers are always a great way to go)! There will be some table surfaces and some sitting/standing room. Unfortunately we do not have easels, drawing boards, or other supplies to offer. 

Our model for February is Addison Sharpe (they/them). Addison is visiting from Minneapolis and has over a decade of figure modeling experience. They’re also just an absolute gem of a human and I’m so excited that they’ll be modeling for us. 

This is not an instructed class, but a space for queer artists of all skill levels to practice drawing from life and honor our bodies in an exclusively queer setting.  Because this is a community event, we charge only to compensate our models and to cover minor processing fees. If you cannot afford to participate, send us an email, we want this to be accessible to everyone! Tipping the model is always appreciated. 

Space is limited! Purchase a ticket via Daffodill’s website (I also posted the link in my bio).

*Masks required for participants, model may be unmasked. 

*To avoid disruption we cannot accommodate late arrivals to the session.
“Home” for Ben. Swipe for a fun warpy photo. Thanks so much for booking a secret flash appointment!

One of my abstract flash pieces on four different clients (for my repeatable flash I typically tattoo the same design 2-4 times). I love seeing where folks choose to put these more fluid designs. Thank you all so much!
Dotwork thorny branch from a couple weeks ago. Thank you Eloise for coming back for yet another piece ! 🖤

Surreal still life from my flash for an incredibly sweet return client. This was a two session project, so all of the lines and the dotwork in the chain and fabric are all 2 months healed- dotwork in the apple and moth are fresh. 

Jenna, it’s an honor as always to add to your collection! I couldn’t be happier with how this turned out (although I got too excited to photograph so please ignore the little smudge of ink I forgot to wipe, whoops).
Got to finish this big northern gannet piece yesterday! Two sessions, all of the lines + dotwork on the head/neck are healed, the rest is fresh! Can’t thank you enough, Robin. ❤️‍🔥
Tricky to photograph placement, but I’m so happy I got to do this crying rabbit from my flash today. Thanks Em!
Love this energy. From a fellow crybaby, thank you so much Madi for choosing this piece!

It’s my 30th birthday today, which feels both very right and totally nuts. When I was just a little baby queer, envisioning my future self was nearly impossible. I never could have imagined that this is what 30 would look like for me, or that I would have even made it to this point at all, honestly. This year started with some difficult shifts, but I can say with confidence that the theme of my heart and this new decade of my life is still “abundance”. Im so grateful for the people in my life who love me well, to have a career I’m deeply passionate about, the fact that my dog of 15 years is still kickin, and so much more. Mostly, I’m proud to have grown into someone that holds nothing but compassion for the younger versions of myself. Also I’m the hottest and gayest I’ve ever been - truly thirty, flirty and thriving ! 

Here’s a photo of me in my very messy studio with a half finished self portrait in the background. ✨
One from the secret flash book. Thank you Madi!
Crying dog from my flash, thank you so much, Brendalyn! A bit wrappy, swipe for angles.
Alex and her mom wanted to get matching tattoos of this flash piece. It was such a sweet experience! Swipe for close ups and some different angles of Alex’s tattoo. Thank you both so much. 🖤
Rocks for Kyvan ! Chosen from the mix and match rocks in my secret flash book. Such a treat doing this for you!
Big abstract negative space starscape, finished after two long sessions! Thank you Madeleine for sitting through five trillion dots ✨

This was Mia’s first tattoo! Super surprised that we managed to finish this in one go- Mia, you’re a total badass for sitting through 4.5 hrs of dotwork like it was nothin. Thank you for letting me create this piece for you! 🌱 I worked bottom to top on this one, so the bottom half is less irritated while the top half is a bit angry still - looking forward to seeing this one all healed and settled in!
Figures from my secret flash book ~ Love this one a lot, thanks Hannah!
A little stinky baby!!! Thank you Steph 🦨

Little abstract blast-over situation on @ibupropain for my half of our trade. They tattooed the lighter piece on themselves a while ago and we overlayed this design to change things up. Love how this one fits the space. Thanks so much Hannah! ✨
Greyhound for Reade! Thank you so much. Swipe to see the Audubon wolf we did a couple years ago.

“Again, again” 

Had a cancellation this morning that no one on the waitlist could fill so last minute so I took the opportunity to tattoo myself. ✨ Thanks for the trust, I sat like a champ. 

Having a lot of feelings about existing in the world right now, so this was some much needed self care. In this life and the next and the next I’d choose my transness again and again and again. 

Above a healed piece by @titcrab333 !
Funky hand with a dandelion from my secret flash. No dots in this one, can you believe it! Thank you @ochrestar

I have complex feelings about visibility that I don’t have the words for at the moment, but I’m here to say that I wouldn’t trade being trans for anything. Each day spent in this transsexual body is sacred. To my trans friends and partners and lovers - getting to love and be loved by you makes existing in this world worth it. For those who don’t feel safe being seen today (and honestly how many of us can say that we do right now) I love you.
Philodendron mexicanum leaf for my sweetest bub @small____hands. I think this is the tenth time I’ve tattooed them? Wild. Thanks for lettin me draw all over yah, pal. 🖍️

I don’t think I ever posted this one and I love it! This design has been retired from my secret flash book, but here it is twice. First photo is on my lovely friend @riversteeth, go get tattooed by them!

Seriously so stoked on this custom piece for the very sweet and talented @moonfriendstudio ! Thank you so much for letting me do this piece for you, couldn’t be happier with how it turned out! Swipe to the end for a healed budding rose.
It’s been a minute since I’ve dropped new flash and opened my books! Mark yer calendarssss.
Butterfly portal for Kiarra! Thanks for letting me blast your knee and for sittin like it was absolutely nothing. 🦋
This one made me really happy 💘 thanks Camille!

Join us for this month’s Queer Figure Drawing session! Sessions take place at @daffodillstudios, which is a queer owned art studio specializing in ceramics (they offer a whole bunch of creative classes and workshops, make sure to check them out!)

Figure drawing is an excellent way to practice observational drawing. Sessions include a variety of quick gestures, short poses, and a few medium/longer poses. Bring a sketchbook or paper on a drawing board and your medium of choice (charcoal, pencils, or markers are always a great way to go)! There will be some table surfaces and some sitting/standing room. Unfortunately we do not have easels, drawing boards, or other supplies to offer. 

This is not an instructed class, but a space for queer artists of all skill levels to practice drawing from life and honor our bodies in an exclusively queer setting.

We have workshopped the price a bit since our last session - tickets are now $16 (which pays the model and our use of Daffodill’s space). We are trying to keep costs as low as possible for participants while making sure everyone is being compensated fairly. Tipping the model is always appreciated. 

Space is limited! Purchase a ticket via Daffodill’s website (I also posted the link in my bio).

*Masks required for participants, model may be unmasked (although this months model will likely be masked as well!) 

*To avoid disruption we cannot accommodate late arrivals to the session.

I really haven’t been tattooing much this summer. Between moving to a new house in a different part of town and trying to prioritize outside activities and time with family and friends, I’ve found I haven’t had a lot to share here lately. Most of my appointments these days are secret flash, so I don’t share many of them (otherwise it wouldn’t be secret 🤓), but here’s a secret flash flower from a few months ago above some healed rocks! 

I’m out of town for a little while and then my work schedule will return to normal for a bit and I’ll hopefully have more tats to share with y’all. Thanks for your support even when I’m less active on this app, it means the world. ✨

Three vessels for Dylan ! I love this design so much and I posted a little vid earlier when I tattooed it on my pal Danni. I ended up only booking this design twice (I generally only book repeatable designs 2-4 times) not realizing that both of the folks getting it are good friends and this is actually the second time they’ve unintentionally gotten matching flash pieces from me. Thank you both for letting me give you a surprise friendship tattoo yet again 😎

Framed flower from my secret flash for Christina ~ thanks for coming in for another secret flash piece! Swipe for some beautifully healed rocks and swipe again for a super close up of one of the rocks so you can see all of that subtle detail. 😎

Rocks for Liz. Thank you!

I brought back some old fav flash pieces just for this guest spot and also have a brand new surreal piece that I’d love to tattoo. I have very limited spots available, please read over the info in this post and check out my story highlights for pricing. Can’t wait to tattoo all you midwestern cuties!! 💘 (Selfie for the algorithm, you know how it goes don’t judge me)

Wahoo! My custom books are open for the first (and likely only) time this year! Books will remain open until 10am on Oct 2 - submit a booking form with whatever your heart desires within that time frame and you’re golden. 

This is a highly selective process, as I can only take on a handful of customs, but it truly doesn’t hurt to submit a form. Even if I can’t get to you this time, I love seeing what ya’ll are envisioning and really appreciate the ideas you bring to me.✨ 

Please review my Fall Booking Updates highlight for relevant booking info. The big thing to know is that I schedule customs over a period of a few months (in this case Oct 2023 - Jan 2024). Flexibility is key here but if you have a specific month you know works best for you, feel free to let me know in your booking form and I’ll do my best to accommodate. 

Lookin forward to drawing for y’all! ❤️‍🔥

I have a few copies of my new zine “Lithic” left! 

It’s a simple 4x4 24 page riso printed collage of some of my favorite rocks that I’ve found over the years paired with some of my recent writing. If you like rocks and feeling all of the feelings about existing on earth in this weird soft human body, then you’ll probably appreciate this humble little zine. 

$12 (includes shipping) - shoot me a DM to purchase one! 🪨 🖤

Thank you to the cuties at @outletpdx for printing these for me!
Okay last flash of 2023 for real this time! These are all available to book for Feb 2024. Please see my story for details/pricing. Cant wait to tat y’all in the new year ~

2023 wrap up - ft some tats I did (including a scuffed up post mud wrestling photo of the one I gave myself this year), some people I love, and of course the queen of my heart: my sweet grandma dog, who is somehow still hanging out. Thanks for being here with me 🖤 

(Mud wrestling and dog photos courtesy of my pal @wondrashoots)

A: pink on cream paper
